<h2 class="tab">
    <a class="tabLink" href="javascript:g.void();" onclick="tab.showTab(this);">Pathfinders</a>
</h2>

<div class="tabData noDisplay ">
    <br />
    Click on the squares to modify the path:<br />
    <br />

    <input type="checkbox" id="PathFinderMinPath" name="PathFinderMinPath" onclick="init();" /><label for="PathFinderMinPath">Limit the number of paths?**</label>
    <br />
    <br />
    <div id="PathFinderDisplay"></div>
    <br />

    <input type="button" value="Shortest Path" id="PathFinderShortest" onclick="DisplayPath(shortestPath);" />
    <input type="button" value="Longest Path" id="PathFinderLongest" onclick="DisplayPath(longestPath);" /><br />
    <br />
    <span style="font-size: smaller;">When displaying the longest and shortest paths, if multiple<br />
        options are available, the first path found (long or short) is shown.
    </span>
    <br />
    <br />

    <div id="PathFinderOtherList">
        still calculating paths...
    </div>
    <br />
    <br />
    <span style="font-size: smaller">**When limiting the paths, as the program finds valid
        <br />
        paths it will only continue to look for paths that are
        <br />
        shorter than the currently found path(s). Any paths
        <br />
        longer the the current shortest path will be discarded. 
        <br />
        As such, the total number of paths available, as well
        <br />
        as the "Longest Path" option won't be a true reflection
        <br />
        of the actual results.
    </span>
    <br />
    <br />

</div>
